HEADWORD: Saccade
<hw>Sac*cade"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.]</ety>
<fld>(Man.)</fld> <def>A sudden, violent check of a horse by drawing or
twitching the reins on a sudden and with one pull.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Saccate</ent>⟦br⟧
